<a name=L10000></a><a href=#L10001>So</a>: U-af
From: ben@dha.unon.org
Newsgroups: africa.horn
Subject: Yemen: Rain/Floods DHA-01 18-Jun-96 (fwd)
Date: 24 Jun 1996 10:45:29

From: Ben Parker  ben@dha.unon.org 
Subject: Yemen: Rain/Floods DHA-01 18-Jun-96 (fwd)



                                   YEMEN
                           HEAVY RAINS - FLOODS
                     DHA-GENEVA SITUATION REPORT NO. 1
                               18 JUNE 1996



  1. GENERAL SITUATION:

    FROM 14 TO 16 JUNE HEAVY RAINS AND FLOODS STRUCK ALL PARTS OF
  YEMEN CAUSING EXTENSIVE DAMAGE TO MANY VILLAGES, TOWNS AND CITIES
  ACROSS THE COUNTRY. FOUR GOVERNORATES, SHABWAH, HADHRAMOUT, MAREB
  AND ALJAWF WERE HEAVILY HIT AND THE GOVERNMENT OF YEMEN DECLARED
  THE ABOVE GOVERNORATES DISASTER AREAS. ACCORDING TO A DECEMBER 1994
  CENSUS, THE TOTAL POPULATION OF THESE GOVERNORATES IS 1.9 MILLION
  PEOPLE OF WHICH 65 PER CENT ARE IN RURAL AREAS. INITIAL REPORTS
  FROM THE AFFECTED AREAS INDICATE THAT THE DAMAGE WAS VERY SERIOUS.
  EIGHTY (80) PEOPLE HAVE BEEN KILLED BY THE FLOODS AND MANY OTHERS
  INJURED. AS YET UNSPECIFIED, A LARGE NUMBER OF HOUSES WERE TOTALLY
  DESTROYED AND WIDESPREAD DAMAGE WAS CAUSED TO BUILDINGS, HOSPITALS,
  ROADS, BRIDGES, EQUIPMENT, COMMUNICATION LINES,  WATER SUPPLIES AND
  AGRICULTURAL LAND.

  2. NATIONAL RESPONSE:

    THE GOVERNMENT AND THE RED CRESCENT HAVE INITIATED IMMEDIATE
  RELIEF ASSISTANCE WITH TENTS AND BLANKETS. HOWEVER, MORE FOOD,
  MEDICAL SUPPLIES, SHELTER AND WATER TANKS ARE URGENTLY NEEDED FOR
  THE FLOOD VICTIMS. THE INJURED WERE TRANSFERRED TO HOSPITALS IN THE
  CAPITAL SANA'A. THE PRESIDENT OF YEMEN HAS IMMEDIATELY FORMED A
  MINISTERIAL COMMITTEE CONSISTING OF FOUR MINISTERS TO SURVEY THE
  DAMAGE AND REPORT TO THE GOVERNMENT WITHIN 72 HOURS. ON 17 JUNE,
  THE GOVERNMENT ISSUED AN APPEAL FOR INTERNATIONAL HUMANITARIAN
  ASSISTANCE TO HELP THE AFFECTED POPULATION. THE UN/DHA RESIDENT
  COORDINATOR AND UNDP RESIDENT REPRESENTATIVE MET WITH THE PRIME
  MINISTER OF YEMEN TODAY 18 JUNE TO DISCUSS THE EXTENT OF DAMAGE AND
  UN ASSISTANCE DURING THE EMERGENCY PHASE.

  3. COUNTRY-LEVEL INTERNATIONAL RESPONSE:

   THE UN IS COORDINATING WITH THE YEMENI GOVERNMENT AND
  INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS  A COLLECTIVE RESPONSE FOR PROVISION OF
  EMERGENCY RELIEF. A MEETING OF THE UN DISASTER MANAGEMENT TEAM
  (UN-DMT) TOOK PLACE THIS MORNING TO COORDINATE THE UN RESPONSE TO
  THE DISASTER. ANOTHER MEETING OF THE UN TEAM, INCLUDING NGOs
  PRESENT IN YEMEN, WILL TAKE PLACE LATER TODAY TO AGREE ON A PLAN OF
  ACTION FOR RAPID ASSESSMENT AND EMERGENCY RELIEF ASSISTANCE.

  4. REQUIREMENTS FOR INTERNATIONAL ASSISTANCE:

    URGENTLY NEEDED RELIEF ASSISTANCE INCLUDES COOKING UTENSILS,
  SANITATION, MEDICAL SUPPLIES, MOBILE WATER TANKS, SUPPLY OF CLEAN
  DRINKING WATER, FOOD, BLANKETS AND SHELTER.

  5. CHANNELS OF DELIVERY OF INTERNATIONAL AID:

    THE GOVERNMENT HAS THE CAPACITY TO DELIVER EMERGENCY ASSISTANCE
  PROVIDED BY INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS. THE MINISTRY OF DEFENCE
  AND THE MINISTRY OF INTERIOR/CIVIL DEFENCE ARE CURRENTLY ENGAGED IN
  THE RELIEF EFFORT. SINCE ROADS AND BRIDGES HAVE BEEN SERIOUSLY
  DAMAGED OR DESTROYED, THE MENTIONED MINISTRIES ARE USING THEIR
  AIRCRAFT AND HELICOPTERS FOR SURVEYING THE AREA DAMAGED AND
  DELIVERING EMERGENCY ASSISTANCE.

  6. INTERNATIONAL PLEDGES AND CONTRIBUTIONS:

    UNDP IS IN A POSITION TO IMMEDIATELY DISBURSE US DOLLARS 50,000
  TO HELP THE GOVERNMENT OF YEMEN TO COORDINATE INTERNATIONAL
  ASSISTANCE AND TO ATTEND TO SOME OF THE RELIEF NEEDS. OTHER
  ORGANIZATIONS SUCH AS CARE INTERNATIONAL, OXFAM AND SEVERAL
  EMBASSIES IN SANA'A INDICATED THAT MOBILIZATION OF ASSISTANCE IS
  UNDERWAY.

    DHA IS PREPARED TO SERVE AS CHANNEL FOR CASH CONTRIBUTIONS TO BE
  USED DURING IMMEDIATE RELIEF PHASE. FUNDS ARE SPENT IN COORDINATION
  WITH RELEVANT ORGANIZATIONS OF UN SYSTEM, AND DHA PROVIDES DONOR
  GOVERNMENTS WITH WRITTEN CONFIRMATION ON UTILIZATION OF FUNDS
  CONTRIBUTED.

    FUNDS SHOULD BE TRANSFERRED TO DHA ACCOUNT NO. C0-590.160.1 AT
  SWISS BANK CORPORATION, CASE POSTALE 2770, CH-1211 GENEVA 2, WITH
  REFERENCE: YEMEN - HEAVY RAINS, DHA-GENEVA.

    FOR COORDINATION PURPOSES, DONORS ARE REQUESTED TO INFORM
  DHA-GENEVA, AS INDICATED BELOW, OF BILATERAL RELIEF
  MISSIONS/PLEDGES/CONTRIBUTIONS AND THEIR CORRESPONDING VALUE BY
  ITEM.

  TELEPHONE NO: +41-22-917.12.34
  IN CASE OF EMERGENCY ONLY: TEL. NO. +41-22-917.20.10
  DESK OFFICER: MS. S. METZNER-STRACK, DIRECT TEL. +41-22-917.21.44
  PRESS TO CONTACT: MS. M. MOULIN-ACEVEDO, DIRECT TEL.
  +41-22-917.28.56
  TELEX: 414242 DHA CH
  E-MAIL: DHAGVA AT DHA.UNICC.ORG

  DPR 310 ROY'96 (1)

                   = DEPARTMENT OF HUMANITARIAN AFFAIRS +



