<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Waldorf Wave</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/waldorf.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/wave.jpg">
<h1>WAVE</h1><hr>
The Wave is an instrument that inspires an emotional
reaction from all who encounter it. When you first see
the Wave (which won the Nordrhein Westfalen Design
Center's Intemational Award for Quality in Design), it
leaves you with the unshakeable impression that this
device is truly unique. Its no-nonsense control features
provide instant, intuitive access to the heart of the
Wave Synthesizer, the Wavetable Engine, with up to 96
oscillators, 96 wavetable generators, 48 analog
multimode filters and the option of analyzing and
editing sounds, right down to the smallest audio atom.
The Wave's large graphic display illustrates every
function graphically and numericaIly for every type of
operation and provides you with a transparent view of
the links between the internal modules. The word
compromise used in conjunction with the Wave is a
contradiction in terms. In addition to its unrivalled audio
quality, it provides you with intuitive access to sounds
that in the past were onfy possible via the dassic
modular systems .This is no coincidence, since the Wave
is also a modular system. When you purchase a Wave,
you know your investment will be safe in the long run.
The Wave features an upgradeable number of voices (16
in the basic version, up to 48 voices in the top-of-line
version). We also now offer exclusive Custom Line
versions and you can have us build a Wave to your
specifications. We will continue to support you and your
one-of-a-kind Wave with, for instance, future hardware
upgrades, and when you consider how impressively the
Microwave itself has retained its value, you can be sure
that the Wave is an instrument with lasting impact that
will remain at the cutting edge of music.<p>
<hr>
<h2>CUSTOM</h2>
The exclusive Wave Custom Line facility offers you a
Wave built to your very own personal specification.
Each Custom Line Wave can be assembled exactly as
you want it from the following unique options:<br>
<hr>
Need more Wave power? With its modular hardware
layout, the number of voices inside your Wave can be
increased from16 in the basic version up to 32 or even
48 voices in the Custom Line versions by simply
plugging in 1 or 2 <b>PLUS16 voice expansion</b> sets.<br>
<hr>
61 Keys not enough? One of our most requested
Wave features is now available. <b>MoreKeys</b> means the
addition of exactly 15 keys (a grand total of 76), some
in the lower and some in the upper area of the
keyboard (from E to G). The width of the MoreKeys
casing is 1340 mm, only154 mm more than the basic
61-key version. All MoreKeys Waves, as an added
feature, also include a professional flightcase.
<hr>
