Date: 30 May 1996 11:41:31 -0500 (EST)

From: support (Web User Support)

Forwarded message:
> From ice.LakeheadU.Ca!msamatas Thu May 23 18:22:04 1996
> Date: Thu, 23 May 1996 18:17:50 +0000
> From: Eistedd Foddor  msamatas@ice.LakeheadU.Ca 
> Subject: aecl and nuclear waste
> To: support@web.apc.org
> Message-id:  8BC3C96E59@ICE.LAKEHEADU.CA 
> Organization: Lakehead University
> X-Mailer: Pegasus Mail for Windows (v2.33)
> Content-transfer-encoding: 7BIT
> Priority: normal
> 
> hello. my name is noel, and i'm part of lakehead university's 
> (thunder bay) environmentalist organization, echo (which can be 
> directly e-mailed at luecho@flash.lakeheadu.ca). i am writing to 
> see if we can get some information.
> here is the story. the atomic energy corporations limited is planing 
> to store nuclear waste in the canadian shield, which means in our 
> area. echo is opposed to this and to the philosophy of nuclear energy 
> in general. approval to dispose of dangerous nuclear waste would mean 
> the aecl would have approval to continue producing nuclear power and 
> nuclear waste. we are currently trying to gather information on nuclear 
> energy and the dumpage plan and also trying to get this information 
> out so the public is aware of what is going on. as well, we are contacting 
> local organizations that are concerned about the plan. either alone 
> or with help, we are also taking action through conventional and 
> traditional and non-conventional means.
> we would like to know if you could support us by helping us find 
> information on this matter, helping us to contact sources that would 
> have data, or providing us with ideas for action. as well, active 
> support on your end would be very much appreciated.
> thanks for you attention and we look forward to a reply.
> noel.
> 

