So: U-env
From: brennain@web.apc.org
Newsgroups: energy.nuclear
Subject: U.Mine Decommissioning - Report Out
Date: 05 Jun 1996 10:05:18 -0500 (EST)

 
The panel report from the federal environmental assessment hearing
on the proposals by Rio Algom and Denison Mines to "deommission"
the uranium mine tailings areas in the Elliot Lake basin (north
shore of Lake Huron, northeastern Ontario) by flooding them will is
expected to be submitted to the federal Minister of the Environment
on June 14, and released to the public on June 19. 
 
Copies of the panel report can be requested from the panel manager
Brian Torrie, at tel 810 997 6364 of fax 819 994 1469; address is
Canadian Environmental Assessment Agency, 13th Floor, Fontaine
Building, 100 Sacre-Coeur Boulevard, Hull, Province de Quebec,
Canada  K1A 0H3.
 
The panel report should be loaded into the agency's home page
(<a href=http://www.ceaa.gc.ca>http://www.ceaa.gc.ca</a> but that will probably take some time. 

