Yuzhno-Ukrainsk/Ukraine, South-Ukrainian Nuclear Power  Plant,
June 11,  -  Third reactor of S-Ukr.  NPP (VVER type) was shut
down on June 8. The explosion of mixed H and O substances took
place in the machine section of the reactor.  The accident was
followed by fire burning from the 3mm pipe in cooling  system.
The fire was liquidated in 12 min, no victims or radioactivity
release, - plant officials told to  special  correspondent  of
ANTI-ATOM PRESS.
     
ANTI-ATOM PRESS,   newsletter   of  antinuclear  activists  in
ex-USSR publishing information on nuclear events and news. The
newscleep above is excluded from AAP N57. Contact: Antinuclear
campaign in ex-USSR,  ed@cci.glasnet.ru 

