From: NENIG  nenig@gn.apc.org 
Newsgroups: energy.nuclear
Subject: Nuclear database on Web
Date: Sat, 22 Jun 1996 14:25:52 +0100 (BST)

The N-BASE Web Site has a searchable database of newspaper 

articles plus news and information on the UK civil nuclear industry 

and related issues, especically reprocessing, nuclear transports, 

wastes and threats to marine environment.  The database has over 5,800

records and is up-dated regularly as are the news pages. The database 

also covers a number of non-nuclear issues where there is a direct or

indirect relevance to nuclear issues.  Please visit.



URL - <a href=http://www.zetnet.co.uk/oigs/n-base>http://www.zetnet.co.uk/oigs/n-base</a>



N-BASE is the information service of NENIG - the Shetland-based

Northern European Nuclear Information Service

.
