<pre>
So: U-env
From: P.DIEHL@OLN.comlink.apc.org
Newsgroups: energy.nuclear
Subject: Re: U.Mine Decommissioning - Report Out
Date: 26 Jun 1996 15:58:00

Content-type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii

The _summary_ of the Environmental Assessment Panel report on the Elliot  
Lake (Ontario) uranium mill tailings area management is now available at:

  <a href=http://www.ceaa.gc.ca/english/panels/ellsum/ellsum.html>http://www.ceaa.gc.ca/english/panels/ellsum/ellsum.html</a>


The panel supports the water cover concept proposed by the proponents and  
attacked by environmentalists (excerpts from summary):

"To establish an effective containment system for the wastes, the panel  
concludes that the tailings must be permanently contained in such a way as  
to insulate them from concurrent exposure to air and water, and to prevent  
their dispersion into the environment.  In the Elliot Lake environment,  
the best way to do this is to keep the reactive tailings permanently water  
saturated."

"The panel recommends that the proponents' proposals, designed to achieve  
such permanent saturation, should form the basis for developing the  
details of a decommissioning licence. However, the panel also recommends  
that there be a number of conditions that should be incorporated into the  
licensing process."

----------------------------------------------------------------------
WISE Uranium Project         WWW: <a href=http://antenna.nl/~wise/wuphome.html>http://antenna.nl/~wise/wuphome.html</a>
