So: U-env
From: psrsm@psr.org
Newsgroups: energy.nuclear
Subject: (Fwd) Feinstein action alert
Date: 28 Jun 1996 17:10:15

From: "Jonathan Parfrey"  psrsm@igc.apc.org 

Dear PSR Supporters of Ward Valley:

Please take a few minutes to respond to the attached Action Alert, 
put out by our colleagues at Americans for a Safe Future.

Jonathan Parfrey
Physicians for Social Responsibility, Los Angeles

***************************************************

ACTION ALERT * ACTION ALERT

Immediate Ward Valley Action Needed

Alaskan Senator Frank Murkowski attempted to force land transfer legislation
that would immediately open the radioactive waste dump at Ward Valley
Wednesday night.  Senators Boxer and Feinstein were able to work with
Majority Leader Trent Lott to remove the legislation from the Department of
Defense authorization bill.  Murkowski vowed to strike again.  He will most
likely make a move in the next month before summer recess in August.  Senator
Feinstein is pivotal.  We need your help to shore up support with Senator
Feinstein to defeat S1596 and any legislation that authorizes a land transfer
to the state.

THE GOAL:  Place 50 calls, write/fax 50 letters, e-mail 50 messages to every
           Feinstein office with the following message:

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Dear Senator Feinstein;

	Thank you for working with Senator Boxer to remove S1596 (Murkowski) from
the Department of Defense bill that would transfer land at Ward Valley,
California for purposes of a radioactive waste dump.  We are now counting on
you to stand shoulder to shoulder with Senator Boxer to defeat S1596.  Your
efforts are essential to protecting our health and safety.  We urge you to
oppose any land transfer to the State for purposes of a radioactive waste
dump.  S1596 is a dangerous bill that would exempt environmental laws,
circumvent the Administration's Supplemental Environmental Impact Statement
(SEIS) process currently underway and prevent the scientific testing
necessary to answer outstanding safety questions.  Additionally, S1596 is a
scandalous attempt by an Alaskan Senator to resurrect the nearly bankrupt
company licensed to construct Ward Valley.  Please work with your Democratic
colleagues to defeat S1596 and any legislation with S1596 as an amendment,
and support the Administration's position of conducting the SEIS process and
additional scientific testing at Ward Valley.  We are counting on you. 


