<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>PMA-5</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/roland.gif">
<img align=left src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/pma5.jpg">
<h1>PMA-5</h1>
<h2>the only portable music production tool that keeps you "in touch"</h2><hr>
<h3>The Roland PMA-5
palm-top music production
system is one of a kind.</h3>
<hr>
<h6><ol>
<li>Never lose or forget another great idea
<li>Get your musical thoughts across easily and instantly
<li>Great arrangements for practice or performance - anytime, anywhere
<li>A very portable sound module to partner your notebook computer
<li>Anyone can use it
</ol></h6>

<h4>Don't be fooled by its compact size.
The PMA-5 is one powerful
production tool. Here's why.
It features an innovative touch-panel
interface and extremely user friendly
operation. It packs an impressive
array of high-quality sounds,
an eight-track sequencer and
a powerful arranger into a unit small
enough to take anywhere. For the
musician on the go, this amazing
palm-sized music production
system is perfect for working out
phrases and taking down musical
memos, all the way up to full-on
compositions and arrangements. It's
also a perfect accompaniment
machine when performing and
practicing.</h4>
<hr>
<h3>A dream user interface.</h3>

The PMA-5 is a unique musical instrument
incorporating a touch-panel. No buttons,
switches or cables to hassle with. Access all
functions from the PMA-5 panel with a touch.
Data can be input via the keyboard display.
To edit, touch the parameter you want to
modify with the pen and drag it up/down to
change values. Creating music was never this
easy or intuitive. The PMA-5 really delivers the
promise of fun music making. It offers a level
playing field for aspiring composers.
<hr>
<h3>Choose an instrument.</h3>

Pick any one of the PMA-5's 306 instrument
sounds and 16 drum kits. These high-quality
sampled sounds have been taken from
Roland's high-end synthesizers. There are
even some brand new sounds. The selection
covers everything from realistic acoustic
instruments to rich synth textures, perfect for
any kind of music. All of the accompanying
instruments including guitars, basses and drum
sets are outstanding. And since the PMA-5 is
28-voice polyphonic, full-scale orchestrations
are easy. This well-thought piece even includes
digital reverb and chorus for adding that
professional touch to your music.
<hr>
<h3>Powerful eight-track
sequencer.</h3>

The PMA-5's sequencer has four melody
tracks and four backing tracks. It holds up to 20
songs or about 21,000 notes, enough to last a
whole set.
<hr>
<h3>Choose a style.</h3>

More than just a practice tool, the PMA-5's
amazing selection of diverse Music Styles are
substantial enough for professional use as well.
100 preset styles, rock and funk variations
included, are provided. Each has six sections
(Intro, Main A, Main B, Fill 1, Fill 2 and Ending)
for a total of 600 patterns. You can also
customize your own patterns and store up to
200 of them in the PMA-5. Simply select and
paste the style you want.
<hr>
<h3>Input your chord
progression.</h3>

Select a root with the keyboard and a chord
type from the 26 choices available. Inversion or
on-bass chords can be specified. Preview it to
make sure it's what you want. You can even
select anticipation for specific beats. You'll be
amazed at how this little music assistant can
effectively interpret everything from traditional
to intricate chord progressions.
<hr>
<h3>Play and record the melody.
</h3>
You've got your accompaniment ready to go.
Now pick your instrument and play the melody
on the touch keyboard to record it in realtime.
As you play the melody, you can drag a note
up/down to apply pitch bend and modulation.
Improvising over your input chord progression
is easy and quick -- just trace over the Ad Lib
bar to left and right. You can also record your
improv into the sequencer. The PMA-5
supports step recording and precise editing as
well.
<hr>
<h3>Putting it all together.</h3>

On the mixer screen you can adjust volume
level, panning, reverb and chorus levels for
each of the eight tracks. Add reverb and chorus
effects to give your music that professional
sound.
<hr>
<h3>Take your music
anywhere.</h3>

The PMA-5 operates on batteries so,
all you need are headphones to access
your personal studio anytime, anywhere.
Inspiration can strike at any time and you
need to be able to take advantage of it
right away! The PMA-5 looks just like an
electronic organizer. It's about the same
size and weighs less than 1.5 lbs./610g.
<hr>
<h3>Use it any way you like.</h3>

Use the Mute button to mute any part for
karaoke style accompaniments. This is
also great for practicing different musical
parts. Connect an optional foot pedal for
hands-free control of playback start/stop.
This is particularly helpful for guitarists.
Connecting a keyboard or sequencer to
the MIDI In turns your PMA-5 into the
smallest GM/GS compatible sound
module ever.
<hr>
<h3>Computer connection.</h3>

Because the PMA-5 has a computer
interface, you can connect it directly to
your computer -- Macintosh or IBM
compatible -- with a single cable. The
PMA-5 can exchange song and pattern
data with your computer, using the
optional PC Communication Kit. This
affords more elaborate sequence editing
using your software-based sequencer.
To minimize equipment hauling, you can
transfer sequence data from your
computer to the PMA-5 and take it to
gigs. Standard MIDI File music data or
your favorite phrase data can also be
loaded into the PMA-5.
<hr>
<h5>For the first time, there is a
musical product whose scope
isn't limited by size or other
logistics. It's there to give you
superior musical assistance
-- anytime, anyplace.</h5>

<hr>
