<pre>
So: U-pol
From: root@kick.knooppunt.be (Postmaster)
Newsgroups: soc.culture.belgium,be.politics,ann.politiek.belgie,be.burgerrechten,ann.media
Subject: Di Rupo must be stopped
Date: 11 Jun 1996 11:46:33 -0000

Di Rupo wants to impose a tax on informationstreams, to finance industry
using a lot of handiwork. He asked the BIPT to quantify these streams.

I think we firmely must protest against this. Di Rupo wants to punish
Internetusers and to discourage the spread of Internetuse.

* New communication technologies do not destroy jobs, they create new jobs.

* New communication technologies give opportunities for democratic debate. 

* New communication technologies open new information resources for
everyone. A democratic state should stimulate the use of these
technologies by making Internet publicly accessible in all libraries. The
discrimination installed between printed and digital information makes no
sense. Digital information is faster and more upto-date, the more it does
not require the demolition of the rainforest.

If people want to plan actions against this vilain attack, they can use a
mailinglist we set up concering cyberrights. 

Send a message to majordomo@knooppunt.be to subscribe.

In the body of the message:

subscribe db

cu,
Daniel Verhoeven.
-- 
KnoopPunt Informatie en Kommunikatie Kollektief vzw        Member of A.P.C.
Snoekstraat 52, B-9000 Gent      tel. 09 233 81 55        fax  09 233 73 43 
Email postmaster@knooppunt.be  Bankaccount 001-2393360-58  VAT 449.519.180
.
