<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>DJ-70</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/roland.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/dj70.jpg">
<h1>DJ-70MKII Sampling Workstation</h1>
<h2>Quality and features for the perfect mix.</h2><hr>

<h5>The DJ-70mkII is an upgraded version of the DJ-70 Sampling
Workstation, which sets the standard for sampling workstations
among club DJs and remix artists. The DJ-70mkII provides everything
you need to create hot mixes, including professional sound quality,
a powerful sequencer, a 37-note keyboard, eight Play Pads,
a Scratch Dial and a large graphic display. In addition, the DJ-70mkII
comes equipped with a built-in SCSI interface, so you can store
and access a virtually unlimited selection of samples on external
devices. Memory is expandable to 32 Mbytes, so you can set
phrase lengths as long as you want, and a new master BPM function
lets you string sampled phrases together at a consistent master
tempo. With all these features, the DJ-70mkII is the natural choice
for club DJs, remix artists and broadcast professionals.</h5>
<hr>
<h3>Features</h3>
<h4>On-the-fly sampling and playback</h4>
With the DJ-70mkII, sampling couldn't be easier. Just connect
an audio source like a CD, tape or microphone to the audio
input, adjust the level and hit the Start/Stop button.
The DJ-70mIIl automatically loops the sample and assigns
it to the 37-note keyboard as well as any of the eight Play Pads,
ready for instant access. There's no complicated setup required.
The large graphic display makes it easy to monitor even the
most detailed editing procedures.

<h4>Professional sound quality</h4>
With 16-bit stereo sampling, the DJ-70mkII offers true CD-quality
sound equivalent to Roland's professional samplers, the S-760/
770/750. You can also choose between two sampling rates --
44.1kHz or 22.05kHz, depending on your requirements.

<h4>Extended sampling times</h4>
With a full 2 Mbytes of memory, the DJ-70mkII provides 22.5
seconds of mono sampling at 44.1kHz. Internal memory is
expandable to 32 Mbytes, enabling sampling times as long
as 6 minutes.

<h4>SCSI interface</h4>
In addition to a floppy disk drive, the DJ-70mkII also features
a built-in SCSI interface, so you can store a virtually unlimited
number of samples on large-capacity storage media and load
and play them at any time. The DJ-70mkII can use not only
hard drives and magneto-optical drives, but also affordable
high-capacity removable media devices that have recently
become available, such as the Iomega Zip Drive and Jaz Drive.
This makes it easy to carry or exchange data just like you do
with cassette tapes. By accessing CD-ROM drives, you can also
take advantage of a vast selection of high-quality samples from
CD-ROM libraries for Roland's S-series samplers.

<h4>Load-While-Playing</h4>
The DJ-70mkII can instantly load data from a hard disk
or CD-ROM while performing. This allows you to load and play
new samples without interrupting your performance.

<h4>On-board 8-track sequencer for quick and easy song
creation</h4>
The DJ-70mkII's 8-track sequencer records and plays back
keyboard input, as well as input from the front panel performance
controllers such as the Play Pads and Scratch Dial. When you
combine the sequencer with the DJ-70mkII's 24-voice polyphony
and 31-part multitimbral capability, you have a complete multi-
instrument mixing and recording console in one compact unit.

<h4>Realtime Phrase Sequence (RPS)</h4>
RPS lets you record a phrase on the built-in sequencer, assign
it to a key or pad, then play it back in real time. This gives you
access to long musical phrases while conserving sample memory.

<h4>BPM function</h4>
The BPM function lets you set your desired sample phrase
tempo easily and quickly by inputting a BPM (beats per minute)
value using the ten-key pad or tap-tempo pad. Using BPM, you
can take various phrases originally sampled at different tempos
and string them together for playback at the same master tempo.

<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>






















