<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Waldorf MiniWorks EQ27</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/waldorf.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/eq27.jpg">
<h1>MiniWorks EQ27</h1>
<hr>
The MiniWorks EQ 27 is a programmable 7-band stereo
equalizer that responds to MIDI commands. It features
top-class sound quality at a truly affordable price. The
equatizer settings may be saved in any of 60 program
locations and can be called via a MIDI Program Change
command. The MIDI channel is randomly definable.
This feature offers you the option of saving an
individual EQ setting for each of your synthesizer's
sounds, which is then automatically called when you
select a given sound. Each of the seven frequency
bands can be addressed separately via MIDI
commands. The two EQ channels may also be
addressed individually. Vou can also use your
sequencer to dynamically automate the EQ 27's
settings - of course without zipper noise. The requisite
adaptations for the popular sequencers' faderpages
are included.
<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>


























