<pre>
So: U-az
From: cscheiner@igc.apc.org
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: ABRI arrests Geronimo Soares
Date: 29 May 1996 22:05:27 -0800 (PST)

From: Charles Scheiner  cscheiner@igc.apc.org 

ABRI Troops Catch East Timor Separatist Rebel

Indonesia Media Network (IMN), May 28, 1996
<a href=http://www.imn.co.id/today/9605/28/28DILI.IMN-e.html>http://www.imn.co.id/today/9605/28/28DILI.IMN-e.html</a>

Dili -- The Indonesian Armed Forces (ABRI) troops had recently caught
a member of the East Timor Separatist Movement (GPK), Geronimo Soares
(31) in the Fatubolu village, Hatolioa subdistrict, Ermera regency.

"Geronimo Soares was ambushed and caught on May 23, 1996 in the
Fatubolu village, Hatolia subdistrict, Ermera regency," said Commander
of Wiradharma Military Command, Col. (Inf.) Mahidin Simbolon in Dili
Monday.

According to Simbolon, Soares, who is dubbed "The long-haired," is a
member of the East Timor GPK from the group which is led by "Sahen"
who wanders in the forests and on the mountain near the Ermera
regency.

"The GPK members of this region is getting weaker and always moves
from one place to another, but we kept on chasing after them," said
Simbolon.

According to Simbolon, the East Timor GPK, both those who surrendered
or caught, before returned to the people were supplied with an
archipelago and national protection concept.

"The archipelago concept which was given to the East Timor GPK before
being returned to the people are shown by our natural behavior so that
they can directly see the form," said Simbolon.

.
