<pre>
So: U-az
From: cscheiner@igc.apc.org
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: Abilio Soares resents Portugal
Date: 29 May 1996 22:05:27 -0800 (PST)

From: Charles Scheiner  cscheiner@igc.apc.org 


Abilio: Portugal Only Left Us with Stupidity and Poverty

<a href=http://www.imn.co.id/today/9605/29/29DILI.TXT-e.html>http://www.imn.co.id/today/9605/29/29DILI.TXT-e.html</a>
Indonesia Media Network (IMN), May 29

Dili -- East Timor Governor Abilio Jose Osorio Soares said, that the
colonial government of Portugal that colonialized East Timor for 450
years, only left a legacy of stupidity and poverty so that the society
had at one time been left very far behind compared to the other 26
provinces of Indonesia.

Governor Abilio said this in a written address which was read by the
Third Assistant of the Regional Secretary of East Timor Abel Dos
Santos Fatima at the meeting of Social Organizations from Jakarta in
cooperation with the Christian Children fund Foundation (CCF) in Dili,
Tuesday.

He said, the colonialism done by Portugal was the most cruel in the
world, because the Portuguese did not educate the people in their
colony so that they can develop.

Because of the colonialism of Portugal, until now the stupidity,
poverty, and backwardness of the people of East Timor can still be
seen and all of that has become the source of the social problems.

The CCF Foundation group led by Sister Flora Situmorang, KYM was in
East Timor to observe the various joint projects with the East Timor
Regional Government in social welfare that has been done for a couple
of years.

Rapid growth

According to Abilio, since East Timor integrated with Indonesia for
the past 20 years has experienced quite a rapid growth.

Touching on the matters faced by this area, the governor said that
they are quite complex.

He gave an example of the program that succeeded in other provinces
may not necessarily work in a condition and situation like the one in
East Timor, so n alternative that is consistent with the condition of
the local area must be found.

In this opportunity, the governor hoped that the CCF Foundation can
increase the review and research of the social problems in East Timor,
so that in the future can develop the programs better and more
consistent with the local surroundings.

"Besides that, the cooperation between the Regional Government of East
Timor with CCF Foundation will be an example for other foundations in
Indonesia," said Abilio Jose Osorio Soares.

Sr. Flora Situmorang, KYM as the Coordinator of the Project , in her
address said that the visit of CCF in this area is to increase the
cooperate with the local government.

The Form of cooperation includes in the sectors of health, education,
environment, and clean water and also economic development.
.
