From: kevmul@dcs.warwick.ac.uk
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: Int. Student Action
Date: 30 May 1996 06:59:57

From: Kevin Mullen  kevmul@dcs.warwick.ac.uk 

From: Kevin Mullen  kevmul@dcs.warwick.ac.uk

on behalf of ASSET(The Association of Students in Solidarity with East Timor)
and Student Supporters of East Timor (SSET) Darwin Northern Territory 
University  

Our groups have been in contact for the past few months with the aim of 
organising some form of co-ordinated international action in support of 
East Timor. We would like to hear from anyone, student or non student, 
who could help us to make contacts with students/ student groups who 
may be interested in taking part.

We have not set a date for these actions yet, but we are considering the 
12th November. We hope that we can encourage people to get involved and 
that this will lead to the formation of more student groups in support of 
East Timor.

			Kev.

If you have any suggestions or can offer any assistance please contact:

Kev - kevmul@dcs.warwick.ac.uk

		OR

Cesarina - crocha@banda.ntu.edu.au

.
