So: U-az
From: Carmel Budiardjo  tapol@gn.apc.org 
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: Belo article in UK Reader's Digest
Date: Fri, 31 May 1996 16:05:10 +0100 (BST)

Belo interview in UK Readers Digest

An article entitled 'East Timor's Reluctant Hero', based on an 
interview of Bishop Belo by Australian-based editor, Paul 
Raffaele, which was published in the April edition of the 
Asian Readers Digest, has been published in the June UK 
edition of the monthly magazine.

With just a few stylistic amendments, the contents are the 
same as the article published in the Asian edition. The text 
was posted on reg.easttimor on 4 April.  

The article is scheduled to appear in other European-
language editions in the coming months.

The article will also appear in the July issue of the Hongkong 
edition.

There are no plans as yet to publish it in the US edition.

The front section of the June edition also includes an article, 
under the 'Behind the Lines' rubric, entitled: 'Meet Us at Ten 
O'Clock Tonight'. This is the same version as that published 
in the Asian edition.

The publication of this article in the Asian Edition resulted in 
the magazine being banned in Indonesia.
.
