So: U-az
From: Comissao para os Direitos povo Maubere  cdpm@gn.apc.org 
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: EU Position on ETimor
Date: Mon, 03 Jun 1996 20:43:55 +0100 (BST)

Source : Publico
Date : 29 May 1996
Dateline : Lisbon
Scope : Unabridged
Original Language : Portuguese
Headline : LISBON AWAITS POSITION ON TIMOR

	Portugal is waiting for the EU's common position on East 
Timor, which has already been approved, to be made public now that 
the hostages, being held by anti-Indonesia rebels fighting for 
independence in Irian Jaya, have been released.  

	The publication of the EU's common position was dependent upon 
the release of the British and Dutch hostages because of fears that 
announcing it might jeopardise the negotiations process.

	Given the hostages were recently released, the Secretary of 
State for European Affairs, Seixas da Costa, stated yesterday in 
Brussels :  "We are waiting for the common position to be announced 
at any moment".  It may well be finally adopted at Thursday's 
meeting of the member states' political directors.

	Although the text of the common position common position has 
not been officially made public, it is said that it expresses 
support for the East Timorese and the process of reaching a 
negotiated settlement on the territory's future.

	According to Seixas da Costa, Portugal had "shown 
understanding throughout, so as to avoid any risk of harm coming to 
the hostages.  We believe that from the moment that issue was 
resolved, conditions then became right for making public the common 
position".  The Secretary of State also said that the question had 
already been put to Portugal's Community partners.
.
