So: U-az
From: calliope@ihug.co.nz
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: ET: SMH on Sumampouw (31 Mar)
Date: 01 Jun 1996 21:25:58

From: calliope@ihug.co.nz (calliope)


Aussie News from Latrobe, 30-May-96
<a href=http://faraday.ee.latrobe.edu.au/~khorsell/OZNEWS/>http://faraday.ee.latrobe.edu.au/~khorsell/OZNEWS/</a>

Federal casino inquiry a farce: Hand

May 21 [The Age]. A former federal Labor minister yesterday hit out at the
Senate's casino inquiry, describing it as a farce and predicting that it would
find nothing adverse against the Premier, Mr Kennett, over the tendering
processes. Mr Gerry Hand strongly condemned the inquiry, and those pushing it,
saying it had its origins as a political exercise.

Mr Hand told The Age he is still furious over what he described as a malicious
campaign waged earlier this year by "people with vested commercial and
political interests" against him and his Indonesian business partner, Mr Robby
Sumampow, the principal shareholder of a Christmas Island casino resort. There
have been suggestions that the inquiry may be widened beyond the Melbourne
casino to include the granting of licenses to the Burswood, Christmas Island
and Brisbane casinos. Mr Hand's comments are bound to infuriate sections of
the federal Labor Party and especially his long-time rival, the Victorian
Senator Kim Carr, who worked with the Democrats' Senator Sid Spindler to
ensure the inquiry was set up. Mr Hand said Australia had a reputation as the
cleanest gaming country in the world, with tight scrutiny and controls.

.
