From: marc@mcr1.poptel.org.uk
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: Peace Camp preceeding Ploughshares
Date: 03 Jun 1996 15:27:36

From: MANCHESTER AREA RESOURCE CENTRE  marc@mcr1.poptel.org.uk 
Subject: Peace Camp preceeding Ploughshares trial

SATURDAY 20th JULY onwards...

**PEACE & DISARMAMENT CAMP**
    British Aerospace Warton, near Preston, England


The 4 women who undertook the "Seeds of Hope - East Timor" ploughshares
disarmament of an Indonesia bound Hawk back in January will be defending
themselves at Liverpool Crown Court from Monday 22nd July. 

Preceeding this trial, there will be a peace camp at BAe Warton (where the
women did the action), with activities for everybody including leafletting
workers, mass trespasses on the runway, and lots more! The peace camp will
start at 10am on Saturday 20th July, continuing through out Sunday 21st, and
will last as long as people wish it to. Hopefully, people will alternate
between taking action at Warton to stop the on-going production and testing
of Hawks for Indonesia, and popping over to Liverpool to watch the women's
trial.


FOR MORE INFORMATION 
  - regarding the trial: tel 0171 923 9511
  - regarding the peace camp: tel Stop the Hawk Deal on 0161 834 0295 or
email         marc@mcr1.poptel.org.uk

.
