So: U-az
From: Carmel Budiardjo  tapol@gn.apc.org 
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: Clandestine plot foiled?
Date: Tue, 04 Jun 1996 23:05:17 +0100 (BST)

Clandestine plot foiled?

Suara Pembaruan, 18 May 1996
Abridged

The military authorities in East Timor claim to have 
uncovered a clandestine plot to burn down and destroy a 
number of key installations in Dili. The military commander, 
Colonel Mahidin Simbolon announced that, following a tip-
off by local people, troops raided a house in Kuluhan, Dili.

Dduring the raid, an LE rifle and seven bullets were found, 
along with five traditional spears, dozens of arrows, a UN 
flag, four other flags, a number of documents and fifty 
molotov bombs.

The army claims that the document revealed a plan to burn 
down a number of armed forces installations, local 
government offices and the TV and radio centres. The action 
was to have been launched on 25 May.

Although no one was arrested, the authorities claim that they 
known the identity of the people involved and expect to be 
able to capture them soon.
.
