From: janerik@forsberg.pp.se
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: Sweden: Swedish support for Indon n
Date: 03 Jun 1996 00:21:52

From: Jan-Erik Forsberg  janerik@forsberg.pp.se 
Subject: Sweden: Swedish support for Indon nomination??
Date: Mon, 3 Jun 1996 09:17:10 +-200

Source: NEWS & VIEWS INDONESIA, Volume 9, No. 83
Date: April 1996
Headline: Foreign Ministers Plan Their U.N. Strategies

This 8-page newsletter is published monthly by:
Embassy of the Republic of Indonesia, Washington DC, under the  =
Department
of Foreign Affairs, Directorate of Information, Republic of Indonesia
The Internet edition is located at:  <a href=http://www.newsindonesia.com>http://www.newsindonesia.com</a>
This information is for educational purposes and may be freely copied =
and
distributed.

Comment from Swedish ET Committee:
Australia did promise to support the Indonesian nomination for the UN =
Sub Commission, in return for support for Australia in the voting for =
the seat in the UNSC.=20
We learned last month that Sweden and Australia were to cooperate =
against Portugal in securing votes for the seats in the SC. In line with =
this agreement, did Sweden now give a similar promise to Indonesia =
regarding support for the Sub Commission nomination?


Foreign Ministers Plan Their U.N. Strategies

Indonesia supports Australia's wish to become a non-permanent member of =
the
U.N. Security Council in 1997,  Foreign Minister Ali Alatas said after
meeting with Downer in Jakarta.  Alatas said that Portugal and Sweden =
were
also seeking non-permanent council membership. The three countries would =
be
competing for two council seats which are becoming vacant soon, he
explained.

Alatas said that in return for support of Australia's bid for the =
Security
Council's non-permanent membership, Canberra would back Jakarta's =
efforts
to join the sub-commission on the Prevention of Discrimination against =
and
Protection of Minorities of the U.N. Human Rights Commission.

Indonesia has nominated Prof. Dr. Muladi and Prof. Dr. Charles Himawan =
for
membership in the U.N. Human Rights Commission. The two are members of
Indonesia's National Commission on Human Rights (Komnas-HAM).

The two foreign ministers also discussed matters affecting the =
Asia-Europe
Meeting (ASEM), the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum and =
the
ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF).
.
