So: U-az
From: fbp@igc.apc.org
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: ETAN Pickets Swedes in NYC
Date: 03 Jun 1996 14:24:18 -0800 (PST)

A dozen people picketed and leafleted outside of the Swedish Consulate in
New York (as well as their Mission to the UN which is in the same building)
on Thursday, May 30 at lunchtime.. One of us wore a sign imitating an
Absolut Vodka ad saying: "Absolut. Terror". 

Some 600 leaflets were handed out to passers by (a number of countries also
have diplomatic offices in the same building as the Swedes, including
Australia. Canada and Ireland). The leaflet called for an end to all arms sales
to Indonesia and to the occupation of East Timor, and urged people to call
or write the Swedish consulate concerning the sale of the naval cannon and
President Clinton concerning the proposed sale of F-16 fighters.

CNN and World Television News stopped by to film, but we don't know if
anything made the airwaves.

John M. Miller
ETAN/NY

