So: U-az
From: Carmel Budiardjo  tapol@gn.apc.org 
Newsgroups: reg.easttimor
Subject: Xanana Gusmao to study law
Date: Fri, 07 Jun 1996 11:49:57 +0100 (BST)

Xanana to study law 

AFP, Lisbon, 5 June 1996

East Timor independence leader, Xanana Gusmao, now 
serving a 20-year jail sentence in Indonesia, has signed up as 
a law student at the university of Coimbra in central Portugal. 
Jose Ramos-Horta, Gusmao's representative abroad,, said 
Xanana wanted to take advantage of his imprisonment to 
improve his higher education.

Ramos-Horta said Indonesian, Australian and US universities 
were prepared to accept Gusmao on correpondence courses. 

'We chose Coimbra because of its historical prestige and 
symbolic importance,' he added. 'We hope that Indonesia, in 
its own interest does not create unnecessary obstacles.'

The university rector, Rui de Alarcao, pledged to resolve any 
problems posed by the Indonesian authorities.
.
