protesting about the plans.
   "The people of this town object to these plans, and rightly
SO," says the mayor of Sergei Posad,  Vasili Goncharov, who is
leading  the  protests.  "We  already  have enough problems to
contend with in this area,  including a radon depository and a
- - - -

Heptyl disposal is not just a Russian problem. Other countries
with missile and space  programmes  also  have  problems  with
ageing  stocks  of  heptyl  since  SO  far  no  technology for
reprocessing has proved to be  environmentally  friendly.  The
facility to be built in Sergei Posad,  some 70 kilometers from
- - - -
the reservoir that the Institute has built for the town, which
contains water that is originally contaminated by heptyl.
   "All the   water   is  filtered  through  our  purification
installations and is SO clean that our children can  bathe  in
it. My grandchildren and I myself swim in it and crayfish live
there."
