Subject: ECODEFENSE!inform press-release
Date: 26 May 1996 23:22:05 +0300

From: ecodefense@glas.apc.org (Vladimir Slivyak)


TO: Media and environmental activists

ECODEFENSE!inform press-agency
Moskovsky pr. 120-34
236006 Kaliningrad/Koenigsberg
Russia
tel/fax 7-0112-437286
e-mail: ecodefense@glas.apc.org

PRESS-RELEASE

"ECODEFENSE!: DIRECT  ACTIONS  AND ENVIRONMENTAL EDUCATION FOR
CHILDREN ARE ONLY WAYS TO PROTECT OUR MOTHER-EARTH"

Koenigsberg/Kaliningrad, May 26

The new   video  at  The  Video  Project  of  ECODEFENSE!,  an
international environmental group,  was issued on May 26, 1996
in Kaliningrad/Koenigsberg  of  Baltic  Sea  region'  part  of
Russia. It's a fifth film is  released  by  the  group  during
1995-1996  in  its  pioneer  project  to educate environmental
activists in   Russia   and   ex-USSR   through   the   video.
     
"Environmental education  -  Metamorphosis",  a new video,  is
looking at  the  problems  of  the  environmental education in
Russia: how  to  organize  that,  to  start  and  continue the
environmental education programmes.  In  the  film,  Alexandra
Koroleva, the    coordinator   for   environmental   education
programmes at ECODEFENSE!  is trying to show new and  original
ways to educate the children in the kindergartens and schools.
It also  is  focused  on  possible  street  actions  with  the
involvement of children, not only room lessons.
     
"If we'd like our children to grow up with the sensitivity for
the nature, if we'd like to get new generations  which will be
ready to  protect  and  save  our  Mother-Earth   -   WE   ARE
ENVIRONMENTALISTS SHOULD  START to run environmental education
programmes everywhere.  In that case,  we'll get the hope that
next generations will love the Earth and do  everything,  even
environmental direct   actions,  to  keep  her  alive",-  says
Alexandra Koroleva.  She spent more than 15 years  to  prepare
and implement  in the schools and kindergartens the children's
programmes about the  nature.  Alexandra  is  also  organizing
regular seminars  for  the schoolteachers,  she is working for
worldwide well-known  IUCN'  commission   on   education   and
communication as representative of Russia.
     
ECODEFENSE! is  expanding  its environmental education program
for last three years and has about  five  kindergartens  as  a
participants in the program. This kindergartens in Kaliningrad
are organizing regular  courses  including  elements  of  deep
ecology for  its  children leading by Alexandra Koroleva.  The
environmental group is also publishing  "Igorny  Dom"  journal
which is focused on new methodics in children' education about
the environment.  The  journal  was  started  by   mid   1996,
two thousands   of   copies   for   each   issue  are  already
distributed. ECODEFENSE!  has  many  more  requests  for  this
journal from  all over the ex-USSR that makes "Igorny Dom" top
popular educational journal at least in Russia.
     
"Actually ECODEFENSE!  is focused on non-violent environmental
direct actions  during  its  history  but  we  are paying much
attention to  environmental  education  because   the   direct
actions and environmental education for children are only ways
to protect  our  Mother-Earth",  -  says   Vladimir   Sliviak,
ECODEFENSE! group chairman and co-founder.
"That's why I'm personally involved in the  video  making  and
the editing  of  that second journal of ECODEFENSE!.  The main
question for the future is  who  will  replace  the  activists
struggling and  defending  the Earth now,  who will be able to
stop corporations or governments from the destruction  of  the
nature. We  sure  that  new  people  will come to continue our
protecting work if we'll  continue  to  educate  children  and
their parents about how beautiful is our Earth", - he ends.
   
For more   information   about   journal,  video,  educational
programmes or ECODEFENSE!  in  general  you  can  contact  the
environmentalists through "ECODEFENSE!inform" press-agency or:
ECODEFENSE!, PO  Box  1477,  236000   Koenigsberg/Kaliningrad,
Russia, tel/fax 7-0112-437286,  ecodefense@glas.apc.org 
     



     
     
     

