	via send-mail with stdio
	id  m0uNzaa-0003zKN@glas.apc.org 
	for ecodefense; Mon, 27 May 96 14:31:52 +0400 (GMT+0400)
	(Smail-3.1.92 1996-Mar-19 #5 built 1996-Apr-22)
Message-Id:  m0uNzaa-0003zKN@glas.apc.org 
Date: Mon, 27 May 96 14:31:52 +0400 (GMT+0400)
From: ecodefense (Vladimir Slivyak)
To: ecodefense, jim.ford@green2.greenpeace.org, ruckus@igc.apc.org, scutting@igc.apc.org
Subject: ECODEFENSE! action update (EDI 86)
Cc: Patrick.Anderson@green2.greenpeace.org
Status: RO

(ECODEFENSE!inform bulletin 86, May 1996, special issue)

ECODEFENSE! group
ACTION UPDATE, June 1996
     

1. NO NUKES

The 1996' spring was focusing anti-nuclear activists  worlwide
for the   commemoration   of  10th  anniversary  of  Chernobyl
accident. The Ecodefenders were also involved in  this  Action
Day. In   Kaliningrad/Koenigsberg   ECODEFENSE!  with  ex-USSR
antinuclear campaign were organizing some events on 26 and  27
of April, such as the meetings of local citizens and youth and
lectures with  Harvey  Wasserman,  well-known  US  antinuclear
activists who visited Kaliningrad that time.  TV was attracted
a lot by. Harvey was giving some interview from Kaliningrad to
american broadcasting stations on 26 of April.  Thanks for the
media work,  Harvey.  We  hope  you'll  be back sometime.

Note for videomakers: video is available from ECODEFENSE!

Also, some   of   ecodefenders   went   to   Kiev/Ukraine  and
participated in the direct action on  23  of  April  when  the
police arrested about 20 activists with unreasonable violence.
Such ecodefenders as Vladimir  Sliviak  and  Nadia  Shevchenko
were jailed  there  for  3  days and trying to make trial over
violent policemen now.

Special edition of ECODEFENSE! journal was published in April,
including different  info-materials  about  Chernobyl disaster
and antinuclear movement.  The Kaliningrad city  looked  great
with red  leaflets ECODEFENSE!' activists putted on the walls.
Chernobyl T-shirts were made in mid-april and  we  still  have
some, but if you'd like to get one - be faster.

Note for videomakers: video is available from ECODEFENSE!


2. ENERGY PROJECT

Three ecodefenders are still working to  prepare  huge  energy
report responding  to  the  questions:  what's  the  renewable
energy sources of Kaliningrad region,  why the region need not
nuclear power,  what's  the  alternatives  to  present  energy
system in the region,  etc. The project is started by mid 1996
and will  be  ended  by December of 1996.  It'll be first same
analysis of the energy system in the region for last 60 years.
The energy  report  will  be  unique source of information for
scientists and activists.


3. ENVIRONMENTAL EDUCATION

The environmental  education coordinators,  Alexandra Koroleva
and Galina Kucheneva,  are running their  educational  program
with kindergarten'  children.  Three  days  per  week they are
talking with children about the  Mother-Earth,  her  ecosystem
and teach  beautiful  childs  how  to live in harmony with the
nature. "The  Green  Way"  program,  Alexandra  prepared   and
implements, is working with children of 5-7 age for full year,
three times per week.  Yet,  Alexandra is regularly organizing
the excursions  and  lectures for the schoolteachers on how to
implement environmental education in the  schools.

Note for  videomakers:  video  of  lessons  and  excursions is
available from ECODEFENSE!

If you're  planning to visit Kaliningrad and would like to see
that educational work - call us and you'll see this  beautiful
educational work.

At present time, Galina Kucheneva is out of the city with some
students to  show them something nice into the environment but
she'll be back soon.

ECODEFENSE! also  issued  new video on environmental education
(see Video Project chapter).

The second issue of new ECODEFENSE! journal  on  environmental
education (Igorny Dom) will be released soon (see Publications
chapter).


4. "YOUTH INVOLVEMENT" PROGRAM AND THE CAMP

ECODEFENSE! continues  to  involve  the youth in environmental
activity. It was about 60 young  people  last  year  who  were
participants at  the  Baltic  Environmental  Youth  Camp  near
Baltic Sea, at national park "Kuronian Spit" near Kaliningrad.
Different workshops  and  practical  environmental  protection
activity (including one street direct action)  were  organized
by the  summer  of 1995 with main goal:  to involve as many as
possible youg people to the environmental  activity  on  local
level.

In 1996, same camp will take place at same place. This time we
are waiting more than  100  participants  from  all  over  the
Kaliningrad region.  Will  be  invited  some  more people as a
guests from the ex-USSR and the Eastern Europe  to  give  some
lectures on  community  organizing.  The  camp will take place
from July 19 to July 28.  Four days before the camp,  on  July
15, the    seminar   on   community   organizing   for   young
environmental activists will take place in  Kaliningrad.  Come
and Enjoy.

Note for  videomakers:  video of the camp in 1995 is available
from ECODEFENSE!


5. "SAVE THE TREES" CAMPAIGN

Most radical  campaign  of  ecodefenders,  organizing   direct
actions to protect the trees, last years mainly in the city,
will be probably reanimated again.  At least,  some  activists
who did  the  campaign  in  1992-1994  came  back  with better
spirit. Some more campaign people are still alive and  working
for ECODEFENSE!  <a name=L10001></a><a href=#L10002>So</a>  maybe this summer will become a nightmare
for the tree cutters and their "new russian" hosts again.

Note for  videomakers:  we  are  planning  to  have some great
action video, contact us later.


6. VIDEO PROJECT

As it  was  announced  the  fifth video of the project is just
released. "Environmental  Education  -   Metamorphosis",   new
video, will  be  soon available on VHS tapes.  18 minutes film
shows how to organize environmental education process with the
children and  even  what's  the street actions you can do with
children, for example on the Earth Day.  Anyway, we think it's
a really  successfull film for those who are interested in the
environmental education methodics with deep ecology  elements.
The ECODEFENSE!'  video-team  is:  Pavel  Malyshev,  Alexandra
Koroleva, Boris Dzasohov, Vladimir Sliviak.

Four previous videos of the project are:
"The non-violent  direct  actions"  -  about history a little,
about present days a little. Mostly about the campaign to stop
the construction  of  oil  terminal  in Ukraine and the direct
action activity during UN climate summit in Berlin/ Germany in
1995. Time: 20 min.
"The seasons  of  the  year:  the  spring"   -   environmental
education video  helping  to  indicate  something  good (first
spring flowers) in something bad (industrial city).  Great for
relaxation (actually  one professional interpreter bought that
for relaxation after hard working days). Time: 36 min.
"My good  actions  on the planet Earth" - video version of the
story that one beautiful child of 6 years  old  wrote  in  the
school. Impossible  to  understand that childs of same age can
think about that. Everyone should look at. Time: 10 min.
"As wolves  die  <a name=L10002></a><a href=#L10003>so</a>  does  freedom"  - it's made for "stop the
murder of wolves" campaign of ECODEFENSE!.  This  campaign  is
started by   December   of   1994   in   Kaliningrad.  Lot  of
publications and some performances were organized during  1995
by this  campaign.  This  film  is  a  video  version  of  the
performance with  same  name   which   was   showed   in   the
Kaliningrad' House   of  Teacher  during  the  celebration  of
professional holyday "Day of Teacher" there.  Some pieces from
the "Thinking  like a mountain" book were used to prepare that
performance. Time: 26 min.

All the videos are in Russian and available from ECODEFENSE!.


7. "STOP THE MURDER OF WOLVES" CAMPAIGN

The campaign  organized some direct actions,  performances and
publications in 1995.  Big critical report on Russian  Law  to
protect the  wild  nature  was  prepared  by the activist last
autumn. At present time the campaign is working on issues  how
to free  animals  from the zoopark.  Last action took place on
the celebration of 100  anniversary  of  Kaliningrad  zoopark,
this spring.  Some  activists  protested against the jails for
animals in the front of Kaliningrad zoopark with  big  banner.
No arrests.

Activists are also preparing the report for the Wolf Federtion
congress which  will take place next autumn in Belgum.  It was
also the idea in the campaign to organize the Action  Day  for
Wolf Protection by December 1. We'll see.


8. PUBLICATIONS

As it  was  announced,  ECODEFENSE!  started  to  publish  new
journal on  environmental  education.  "Igorny  Dom"  (Playing
House), new journal, is focused for new methodics in children'
environmental education with deep  ecology  elements.  It  was
about 2000  copies  of first issue which were distributed very
fast. The journal become a top educational journal in  Russia.
Sent your request if you'd like to have it.

One more  publication  will be released soon.  Maybe next week
already, we'll  have  a  thousand  of  books  describing   the
environmental education  program  which  ECODEFENSE!  runs for
last three  years  in  kindergartens  and  schools.  All   the
methodics, pictures  and more are included in that book which,
we hope,  will  help  to  those  who  are  trying   to   start
environmental educational  work or interested in.  The book is
writed by environmental education coordinators of  ECODEFENSE!
working for  more  than  15 years in this field.  You can also
send your request for to ECODEFENSE!

All the publication are in Russian.


ACTION UPDATE, JUNE 1996: was prepared by team of ecodefenders
you can reach by:
tel/fax 7-0112-437286 or e-mail: ecodefense@glas.apc.org
post address: PO Box 1477, 236000 Kaliningrad, Russia
Find our WWW home page on  <a href=http://cci.glasnet.ru/... >http://cci.glasnet.ru/...></a> but it's
in Russian only.

.
