International Financial Institutes Activities

Belarus: The World Bank

is preparing a Urban Water and Solid Waste Management Project
with the Ministry of Housing and Municipal Services for US $ 30
million to develop a municipal waste treatment and water supply
management program;

is appraising a Petroleum Sector Development Project with
Belarusneft/Belnefteprodukt for US $ 40 million for
restructuring, technology and equipment transfer to rehabilitate
selected oil production facilities.

Estonia: The World Bank

is preparing a Housing Development Project with the Ministry of
Economic Affairs for US $ 15 million to develop the housing
market, longer term housing and finance strategies, and
regulatory reform;

is preparing the appraisal report for an Agriculture Project
with the Ministry of Agriculture and Environment for US$15.3
million to support reform and restructuring of the sector.

Latvia: The EBRD

is preparing a US $ 82.1 million (ECU 104,319,351) Riga
Environment project to finance short term priority investments
in Riga Waterworks. Contact: Riga City Council, tel.
+3712-320-680, fax. +3712-220-785

Lithuania: The World Bank

approved the Siauliai Environment Project with the Ministry of
Environmental Protection for US $ 6.2 million to manage the
river basis water and wastewater;

is preparing a Highway Project with the Road Administration for
US$15 million to expand maintenance, complete by-passes, improve
roads and management;

is completing negotiations on a Geothermal Project with the
Ministry of Energy and Lithuania State Power System for US $
12.8 million to demonstrate geothermal energy as an indigenous
resource to replace imported fossil fuel and to reduce emission
of GHG;

is preparing an Energy Efficiency/Housing Project with the
Ministry of Construction and Urban Development for US $ 10
million to increase energy efficiency in residential and public
buildings, and improve thermal efficiency of existing housing;

processing the appraisal report for an Agriculture Project with
the Ministry of Agriculture for US$30 million to reform and
restructure the agricultural and forestry sectors.

Poland: The World Bank:

is completing negotiations for a Solid Waste Management
Privatization Project for US $ 60 million to improve solid waste
collection in one or two major cities;

is preparing a Geothermal and Environment (Podhale) Project with
Geotermia Podhalanska for US $ 55 million to reduce air
pollution and associated damages to health and environment;

is preparing an Energy Efficiency Project (formerly Power
Distribution) with Integrated Energy Efficiency Improvement for
US $ 100 million to invest in energy efficiency, demand-side
management, and institutional strengthening and restructuring;

is completing negotiations on the Bialsko-Biala Water and
Wastewater Project with the Bielsko Biala Municipal Utility for
US $ 21.5 million for institutional strengthening and investment
for water supply and wastewater systems;

has approved a Power Transmission Project with the Polish Power
Grid for US $ 120 million for investments in transmission and
dispatching;

is preparing a Coal Sector Adjustment Operation for US $ 150
million to close and merge mines, finance mine site reclamation.

RUSSIA:

THE IMF agreed on Feb. 23, 1996 to lend Russia US $ 10 billion
for general economic support despite tragic developments in
Chechnya, under the condition that Russia abolish export duties
on oil and gas. According to the IMF, the duties keep domestic
energy prices in Russia artificially low, when market- oriented
prices would encourage more local energy efficiency. Russia
agreed to change duty policies for gas in April, and for oil in
July, 1996. (Washington Post, Feb. 23, 1996)

The WORLD BANK:

has delayed project processing on the Gas Injection
Demonstration Project with Purneftegas for US$47 million; 

is completing negotiations on the Bridge Rehabilitation Project
with the Federal Highway Department, and Ministry of Transport
for US$350 million to improve the condition of the public road
network;

is preparing a Petroleum Joint Venture Project for US $ 500
million for major new oil field development in Western Siberia;

is preparing a Krasnodar Power Generation Project for US$500
million for a 900MW combined cycle generator;

is appraising a Biodiversity Conservation Priority Response
Program for US$6.2 million to establish a national biodiversity
strategy, assist protected areas, and develop various resource
management strategies for the Lake Baikal region.

THE EBRD is preparing a US $ 73.5 million (ECU 93,326,056) St.
Petersburg Water Development project to improve the reliability
and quality of drinking water in St. Petersburg. Contact:
Vodocanal of St. Petersburg, Felix V. Karmazinov, tel. +7812-
2741090, fax. +7812-274-1361.

