CONFERENCE ON SIMULATION AND GAMING FOR SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT
The International Simulation and Gaming Association (ISAGA) is a
worldwide network of professionals working on and using
simulation/gaming in education, training and research.
Simulation/gaming provides a low-risk context in which the
effects of decisions can be experienced and examined, thus
leading to an understanding of the challenges of sustainable
development. Language: Contact: Valdis Bisters, ISAGA '96,
