   +                                                             .

     
**********************************************************************

ACTION ALERT: TOGETHER WE CAN STOP THE BURN!
                       sITIZENS AGAINST CHEMICAL WEAPONS INCINERATION

7 June  1996 Chemical Weapons Working Group distribute request to sup-
port for senator ford's amendment to senate bill 1745.

DEFENSE AUTHORIZATION AMENDMENT PENDING TO STOP INCINERATION :

Senator Wendell Ford (D-Ky) is poised to submit an  amendment  to  the
1997 Defense Authorization Bill, S.1745, that would do the following:

1) Place  a three year moratorium on contracts by the Army for incine-
rators for CW disposal.

2) Shift $50 Million from  the  incineration  program  to  ALTERNATIVE
TECHNOLOGIES  program  to  demonstrate  non-incineration approaches to
include ALL sites, including CW munitions sites.

3) Change the existing "stockpile elimination  deadline"  of  December
31,  2004 and substitute the U.S.  obligations under the Chemical Wea-
pons Convention, yet to be ratified.

We are seeking your help in getting Co-sponsors for this Amendment. It
has  been  a  12 year battle to stop this program:  NOW IS THE TIME TO
ACT!!

Targets: All U.S.  Senators,  with particular emphasis on  those  from
Oregon,  Arkansas,  Alabama, Indiana, Utah, Colorado, Maryland, Hawaii
and Kentucky (McConnell).

Other primary targets are members of the Senate Armed Services and Se-
nate Defense Appropriations Committees.

Contact for additional information:

John Capillo
Kentucky Environmental Foundation
Chemcial Weapons Working Group
e-mail: KEFCAPIL@acs.eku.edu

**********************************************************************

"CHEMDET-96" :  Chemical Weapons Disposal Conference in Izhevsk  (Rus-
sia, Udmurtia)

June 18,  1996 in Izhevsk have begun the conference "CHEMDET-96". Con-
ference are organized by Russian Academy of Sciences together with the
Government of Udmurt Republic.

The purpose  of conference is to discuss certain ecological and tecno-
logical problems in the context of elimination of chemical weapons  in
Russia.

Organizers are  going  to  give  regular reports about the work of the
conference by e-mail (in the Russian language).

E-mails of the conference: ipm@ipm.udm.ru

For more detailed information about the  conference  "CHEMDET-96"  and
about the reports of the conference you may ask:

J.Adibi, Director of EcoBridge Environmental Programs
         CEC International Partners.
         email: cecny@igc.apc.org

Vadim Petrov,  Union for Chemical Safety, Udmurtia
         email: vadim.petrov@online.mark-itt.ru.

