From: AMARC-Europe  amarc@gn.apc.org 
Newsgroups: reg.eeurope
Subject: AMARC pan-euro radio conference 96
Date: Mon, 01 Jul 1996 21:15:01 +0100 (BST)

 
 
               VOICES WITHOUT FRONTIERS 
               ------------------------ 
 
                        The 2nd 
             AMARC Pan-European Conference  
            of Community Radio Broadcasters 
 
                       COPENHAGEN 
                        DENMARK 
 
               16TH - 19TH OCTOBER  1996 
 
 
                  Jointly organised by: 
                      AMARC-Europe 
                           and  
               Sammenslutningen af lokale 
                radio- og tv-stationer i  
                         Danmark 
 
 
----------------------------------------------------- 
 
ABOUT THE CONFERENCE 
 
The theme for the second AMARC Pan-European conference  
of ommunity radio broadcasters is 'Voices Without  
Frontiers'. It will give particular attention to the  
role of community radio in relation to migrants,  
refugees and ethnic minorities in the context of the  
changes in European political boundaries and the  
rapidly expanding media landscape. The conference will  
offer practical workshops, theoretical debates and  
analytical discussions on the experiences of community  
radio. 
 
'Women's Voices Crossing Frontiers' is the theme of the  
women's day. It will be a chance for women in community  
radio to meet, discuss, interlink and develop strategies
for empowerment to cross frontiers and reach out to the 
airwaves through community radio all over Europe. 
 
There will be much to learn, teach, discuss and challenge 
in this four day event.  If you are interested in 
community radio and its development, be there! 
 
 
OUTLINE AGENDA 
 
Tuesday 15 October:     Welcome dinner for Women Delegates 
 
Wednesday 16 October:   Women's Day: 'Women's Voices Crossing Frontiers'
                        'Voices Without Frontiers' Welcoming Reception 
 
Thursday 17 October:    Opening Plenary 
                        Workshops and Action Meetings  
                        Visits to local stations in Copenhagen 
 
Friday 18 October:      Workshops 
                        Public Meeting: 'Voices Without Frontiers'
 
Saturday, 19 October:   AMARC-Europe General Assembly 
                        Closing Conference Plenary 
                        Closing Party! 
 
 
SUGGESTED WORKSHOPS TOPICS 
 
Ethnic minorities and cultural exchange  
Xenophobia and mother-tongue broadcasting 
Community radio and minority languages  
Frontiers within the station 
 
Good media laws - changing legislation  
Solidarity campaigns for community radio  
International media concentration 
 
Training for women's radio 
Creating new forms of expression  
Community access and participation 
 
Joint projects with other stations  
Programme exchange 
Linking women's priorities in east and west 
 
Editorial integrity in small communities  
Social action campaigns 
Music as a form of cultural expression 
 
Strategic planning and management  
Fundraising ideas 
Advertising on community radio 
 
Community radio in war and repression  
Women journalists in conflict resolution  
Radio from a woman's perspective 
 
Internet - networking for community radio  
Producing radio programmes 
Build your own fm transmitter 
Digital production 
 
Please tell us what you would like included in the  
conference by contacting the AMARC-Europe secretariat.  
We will do our best to facilitate you. 
 
 
CONFERENCE ORGANISER: 
 
Felix Forster 
AMARC-Europe Secretariat 
15 Paternoster Row 
Sheffield S1 2BX, England 
Phone:  +44 114 279 5219 
Fax:    +44 114 279 8976 
E-mail: amarc@gn.apc.org 
 
 
CONFERENCE COORDINATOR IN DENMARK: 
 
Bodil Christensen 
c/o Radio FTF 
Hammershusgade 15, 2.floor 
DK- 2100 Copenhagen O. 
Phone: +45 3929 4445 
Fax:   +45 3929 4485 
E-mail: boc@komc.dk 
 
 
CONFERENCE FEE: 
 
Early Registration (before 15th August):  
AMARC members  70,- Pound Sterling 
Non-members   105,- Pound Sterling 
 
Late registration (after 15th August):  
AMARC members  80,- Pound Sterling 
Non-members   120,- Pound Sterling 
Late fee charge. 
 
 
ACCOMMODATION OPTIONS: 
 
Hotel accommodation is available for 50,- Pound per night  
for a single room or from 25 - 35 ,- Pound per night  
depending on numbers sharing room.  
Hostel accommodation costs 15.00 ,- Pound per night.  
All prices include breakfast and transportation to and  
from conference centre. 
A limited amount of free sleeping space will be  
available. 
 
 
TRAVEL 
 
Scandinavian Airlines, SAS has been appointed the  
official carrier for Voices Without Frontiers and is  
offering all conference participants and accompanying  
persons a special fare to/from Denmark. Please contact  
your nearest SAS office and quote reference number DK  
9652. 
 
 
SOME INFORMATION ABOUT AMARC? 
 
AMARC, the World Association of Community Radio  
Broadcasters, is a world-wide network of community  
radio stations founded in 1983. It is a  non- 
governmental organisation dedicated to the promotion  
and development of community radio world-wide. Its  
members are radio stations, production groups and  
associations of radio stations which operate for social  
purposes and are independent of governments and large  
media organisations. 
 
After several years of increased activity in Europe the  
European members of AMARC launched a European section.  
At the first Pan-European conference which took place  
in Slovenia in September 1994, AMARC-Europe was founded  
as a European Non-Governmental Organisation. Its  
secretariat, currently hosted by the Community Radio  
Association in the UK, coordinates transnational  
projects and programmes carried out by and for its  
members in Eastern, Central and Western Europe. 
 
 
ABOUT OUR HOSTS IN DENMARK: 
 
Sammenslutningen af lokale radio- og tv-stationer i  
Danmark is the Danish Association of Community Radio &  
Television. It was founded in 1984 and today has 70  
members. It includes a wide range of radios from small  
community of interest to larger stations 
broadcasting regionally.  Sammenslutningen has been an  
active member of AMARC since its foundation. 
 
Gladsaxe Municipality is the local authority for a  
region of Copenhagen which lies just outside the city  
boundaries. It has a population of 50,000. This  
municipality is recognised in Denmark for an active  
role in cultural activities and is unique in Denmark in  
having a radio station entirely funded by the  
municipality. 
 
 
MORE INFORMATION, PLEASE 
------------------------ 
 
