Czech police break up blockade of nuclear plant,  PRAGUE, July
8 (Reuter)   -  Czech  police  broke  up  a  blockade  of  the
Soviet-designed Temelin    nuclear    power     station     by
environmentalists on  Monday,  but  protestors said they would
continue the demonstration.

Czech protestors sneak into nuclear plant site, PRAGUE, July 9
(Reuter) -  Environmentalists blockading a Czech nuclear power
station sneaked into the half-completed plant on Tuesday in  a
protest which they said showed gaps in the site's security.

