Subject: STOP SEA NUCLEAR TRANSIT! URGENT! N
Date: 01 Aug 1996 00:08:20 +0300

From: ecodefense@glas.apc.org (Vladimir Slivyak)
Subject: STOP SEA NUCLEAR TRANSIT! URGENT! NEED HELP!

From ecodefense Thu Aug  1 00:05:08 1996
Received: by glas.apc.org
	via send-mail with stdio
	id  m0ulhW0-00041FN@glas.apc.org 
	for ecodefense; Thu, 1 Aug 1996 00:05:08 +0400 (GMT+0400)
	(Smail-3.2 1996-Jul-4 #3 built 1996-Jul-13)
Message-Id:  m0ulhW0-00041FN@glas.apc.org 
Date: Thu, 1 Aug 1996 00:05:08 +0400 (GMT+0400)
From: ecodefense (Vladimir Slivyak)
To: ecodefense, ed@cci.glasnet.ru
Subject: STOP NUCLEAR TRANSIT! URGENT! NEED HELP!
Cc: bleland@igc.apc.org, bradsher.m@applelink.apple.com, ecologia@igc.apc.org,
    ei@igc.apc.org, ekessler@metgem.gcn.uoknor.edu, jdebarde@ccs.carleton.ca,
    kri@igc.apc.org, mdc@essential.org, rts@gn.apc.org, sacredearth@igc.apc.org,
    vbirstein@igc.apc.org
Status: R

URGENT!  URGENT!  URGENT!  URGENT!  URGENT!  URGENT!  URGENT!
TO:
ENVIRONMENTAL AND PEACE ORGANIZATIONS, Nuclear campaigners
MASS-MEDIA and NGO's MEDIA, environmental and business editors
FR:
ECODEFENSE!, Ex-USSR Antinuclear Campaign of  Socio-Ecological
Union
                
SUBJECT: STOP SEA' NUCLEAR TRANSIT !!!
         Action and faxes needed!
     
ON JULY 30, The "Amber-2" ship with nuclear materials (uranium
concentrate) arrived  to  the  waters  of Kaliningrad' region.
There is 19 of 23-f containers with uranium. The ship is going
from Sankt-Petersburgh  port  to the USA,  San-Francisco.

The non-governmental  organizations  are  protesting  the ship
entering to the Kaliningrad' port;  the  ship  is  staying  in
Kaliningrad' territorial    waters   and   waiting   for   the
opportunity to  enter the seaport or for additional directions
from the authorities.
     
There is no any necessary equipment for  the  operations  with
radioactive materials  in  the  seaports  of Kaliningrad.  The
Kaliningrad is not included in the governmental  list  of  the
ports which  can  operate  radioactive  materials.  That's the
violation of the Russian law "On the use of nuclear power"  (#
41) if  the  ship will enter to the port and the port and city
authorities will allow that.  Because of no special  equipment
the port  workers as well as all the population of Kaliningrad
region are  in  very  dangerous  situation  when  even   small
accident will  be  followed  by  very  serious consequences of
radioactive contamination of the land and the sea.
     
Ministry of   atomic  power  of  Russia  (Minatom)  and  their
enterprise "Isotop" (Sankt-Petersburgh) has  a  contract  with
american parties to transport the uranium.  It's still unclear
who are american partners for them.  But clear that Minatom is
trying to  use  the  seaport  of  Kaliningrad  to  transit the
dangerous radioactive   materials.  In  1993  non-governmental
organizations sent to the local parliament the law project for
nuclear-free zone  in  Kaliningrad region and demanded to stop
all the operations with radioactive  materials.
     
The campaign for nuclear free zone is still going on -  please
send your   fax-messages  to  numbers  below  to  support  the
campaign and to prevent extremely dangerous  the  entering  of
radioactive ship  to Kaliningrad seaport!  Below you also will
see the example of protest-fax-message which is  sent  out  by
different ex-USSR NGOs. There you'll see also more details.

If you can also help us to get information about this contract
(who are american contractor,  for what this uranium  will  be
used) - it would be greatest help we need now.
     
Additional information:  ECODEFENSE! and Antinuclear campaign,
Moskovsky prospekt 120-34, 236006 Kaliningrad, Russia.
Tel/fax 7-0112-437286
e-mail: ecodefense@glas.apc.org, ed@cci.glasnet.ru
     
LET'S MAKE TOGETHER NUCLEAR-FREE EARTH !
STOP THE SEA NUCLEAR TRANSIT!
SEND FAXES OF PROTEST TO STOP NUCLEAR TRANSIT FOREVER!

example of letter
     
The head of regional Kaliningrad administration
-  Yury Matochkin (fax 7-0112-463862)
The major of Kaliningrad - Vitaly Shipov
(fax 7-0112-211677)
The chairman    of   governmental   environmental   protection
committee of Kaliningrad - Vladimir Litvinenko
(tel/fax 7-0112-210906)
"Kaliningradskaya pravda" newspaper (tel/fax 7-0112-217733)


We are,  ...  (name of organization)  ...,  sending  you  this
message to protest the sea nuclear transit through Kaliningrad
region. We also protest  Kaliningrad'  authorities  that  they
allow dangerous illegal transit.
     
On 30 of July  "Amber-2"  ship  with  uranium  concentrate  is
arrived to  Kaliningrad'  sea waters.  Because of Kaliningrad'
ports have no special equipment to  operate  with  radioactive
materials this  is  very  possible  that nuclear accident will
take place during operations on the ship in the port.  In case
of accident  the  lands and sea both will be contaminated.
     
The entering of the ship is illegal under russian laws "On the
use of nuclear power" (#41).  We aslo know that the ships with
radioactive materials  illegally  visited Kaliningrad' seaport
about 6 times already. In May of 1996, one soldier of the port
guard died with leukemia diagnosys.  This soldier wrote in own
message (May  11,  1996)  to  the  commander   that   he   was
hospitalized immediately  after  he  guarded  the  ships  with
radioactive materials in 1995.

We demand to stop sea nuclear transit and the  nuclear  threat
to the  population  of  Kaliningrad  and  Baltic  Sea  states.
Kaliningrad authorities, start to act immediately!
     
Signatures,----------------------------------------------------
     
Please, let us know that you send your fax.
ECODEFENSE! and antinuclear campaign in Kaliningrad,
tel/fax 7-0112-437286, e-mail: ecodefense@glas.apc.org
     
--------------------thanks for your support--------------------

     
     

