    wildwood@gn.apc.org
Status: R

TO: environmental and peace organizations
FR: ECODEFENSE! & xUSSR antinuke campaign
Subject: STOP SEA NUCLEAR TRANSPORT, NEWS, message 2


August 2, 1996
THE SHIP WITH RADIOACTIVE MATERIALS ENTERED NOT THE PORT STILL!

Campaign of environmental protests is still keeping the ship 
"Amber-2" with uranium (?) out of Kaliningrad' port. 
The ship arrived to Kaliningrad' waters on July 30 from 
Sankt-Petersburgh and having the target San-Francisco, USA. 
Environmentalists demands to close port for all the ships with 
radioactive materials in the future and to send "Amber-2" out of
Kaliningrad' territorial waters. The ship is staying near the 
water entrance to the seaport fourth day. 19 containers with
uranium concentrate are waiting for the accident.
There is no any equipment for operations with radioactive materials 
in the port, there is no trained people who know how to organize
the protection of workers from radioactivity and the prevention
of accidents in the port. On 20 of May, 1996, the soldier died
from leukemia - he guarded same ship with radioactive materials
in 1995 at Kaliningrad seaport.
The ship has no own guard (the seaport too) and any terroristical 
act will result as contamination of the sea and the lands.

DEVELOPMENTS

As we know from the message of the director of the Kaliningrad' 
seaport (we've got on July 31) the Head of Kaliningrad regional 
administration - Yury Matochkin signed the document (some monthes
ago) forcing the port administration to serve nuclear ships. It's,
of course, giving him not better chances to win next elections this
autumn. 
The source at MCHS (Ministry of Accident Situations) told us today
that MCHS inspectors are not sure that Minatom (Ministry of Atomic
Power) told them the truth about that ship. It's possible that the 
ship transports nuclear wastes!
The source at Nature Protection Committee of Kaliningrad informed
that the uranium (if it's uranium) is from Kazakhstan, not russian.
The port authorities reports that the ship must stay in the seaport 
untill August 5. Then it will go away to San-Francisco.
The port authorities said that the ship must take from Kaliningrad'
seaport unknown equipment and the cars.

MEDIA

Since the press-release, environmentalists sent out on July 30,
american radio "Svoboda" (Freedom) and Radio of Russia distributed
information about the ship to all around former USSR. The main 
political newspaper in Russia "Izvestia" is preparing the article 
at present time. Local media in Kaliningrad published and broadcasted
a lot. Like governmental radio agency in Kaliningrad broadcasted very
environmentalist-friendly special news issue this morning. 

INTERVIEWS

Last 3 days we interviewed some officials in Kaliningrad:
Correspondent: Do you know about the ship with uranium?

1. Regional administration:
No answer.

2. Vice-Major of the city: 
Uranium? it's terrible! what to do?

3. Regional committee of nature protection: 
No, we know about this ship nothing.

4. Gosatomnadzor (nuclear control organization of president): 
It's not dangerous.
Cor.: How do you know? Have you any information about the ship?
G.: No, we have no information, but it's not dangerous.

5. The port authorities:
The head of regional administration commanded to organize the
service for this ship. We should work on this ship or we'll loose
our jobs.


ACTION

Please, send your faxes to all the numbers we gave you in alert-messgage!
If you have not this message, we'll send you copy again - just let
us know. Since July 30, several ex-USSR and US NGOs sent some faxes.
Thanks a lot. And we still need more! We need your support now!
We demand the nuclear-free zone in Kaliningrad region.

Let us know about your support:

ECODEFENSE!, Moskovsky pr. 120-34, 236006 Kaliningrad/Koenigsberg,Russia,
Tel/fax 7-0112-437286, e-mail: ecodefense@glas.apc.org

x-USSR Antinuclear Campaign, Socio-Ecological Union, PO Box 211, 121019
Moscow, Russia. Tel/fax 7-095-2983087, e-mail: ed@cci.glasnet.ru

NO NUCLEAR TRANSPORT AT SEAS!

Prepared by Vladimir Sliviak
In Moscow

.
