SPECIAL ISSUE: ALEXANDR NIKTIN - HALF A YEAR IN KGB CUSTODY
               ALEXANDR LEBED ASKS PROSECUTOR ON NIKITIN
---------------------------------------------------------------

ALEXANDR NIKITIN, AUGUST 6, 1996: HALF A YEAR IN KGB CUSTODY

On August 6,  Bellona co-worker Alexandr Nikitin has been held
in custody in the FSB prison in St. Petersburg for six months;
after having been arrested on charges of espionage on February
6, 1996.

Since then,  the  Russian security police FSB - formerly KGB -
has committed a series of judicial and human rights violations
against the environmentalist. The case has achieved noticeable
attention internationally,  and several important persons  and
institutions    have    voiced   criticism   towards   Russian
authorities.

Nikitin has been jailed because of his work as co-author on  a
report  on the nuclear hazards of the Russian North Fleet,  to
be launched in its final edition  by  Norwegian  environmental
foundation  Bellona  on August 15.  The FSB accuses Nikitin of
having  disclosed  state  secrets  for  payment.  Nikitin,  in
addition  to his present occupation as environmental activist,
is a pensioned captain of 1st rank in the Russian navy.

As an employee of the Bellona  Foundation,  Nikitin  obviously
has  received  payment.  The  report  on  the  Northern Fleet,
however, is based on open sources in its entirety.

The indictment  is  based  on  alleged  breaches  against  two
decrees  from the Russian Ministry of Defence.  The decrees in
question are <a name=L10001></a><a href=#L10002>so</a> secret,  that Nikitin's lawyer,  after half  a
year, has not been allowed to see them.

The paragraph  in  question - Z 64 of the Russian Penal Code -
states Death Penalty as one of its punishmental options.

_______________________________________________________________
ALEXANDER LEBED ASKS PROSECUTOR GENERAL OF RUSSIA TO LOOK INTO
NIKITIN CASE

On July  19 a group of deputies of the Russian Parliament made
a request to Secretary of Russian Federation Security  Council
Alexander  Lebed  concerning  legal  proceedings  in Alexander
Nikitin case.  The request was passed by the majority of  Duma
members and was delivered to Alexander Lebed on July 22.

On July   26   Lebed  responded  to  the  request  asking  the
Prosecutor General of Russia Juriy Skuratov  to  consider  the
deputies request.  On July 31 the Office of Prosecutor General
of Russia declared that they were  going  to  investigate  the
case  and  report  about  the results to the deputies of State
Duma.

Alexander Nikitin is Bellona's co-worker who was arrested  and
accused of espionage by FSB and has been kept in FSB's custody
in St.-Petersburg for  half  a  year  till  now.  The  charges
against  Nikitin are based upon chapter 8 of the new Bellona's
report "The Russian Northern Fleet -  sources  to  radioactive
contamination   of   the  region".  The  chapter  reveals  the
information   on   the   accidents   onboard   nuclear-powered
submarines.
_______________________________________________________________
Additional information: bellona@sn.no
