Subject: GAMA: bulgaria-neckermann
Date: 21 Aug 1996 08:59:00

Content-type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii

        GLOBAL ALTERNATIVE MEDIA ASSOCIATION - GAMA - PRESENTS:
        -------------------------------------------------------
                news provided via our member "infoPool"
                --------------------------------------

SOURCE: BTA
HEAD:   neckermann to invest in bulgarian hotels

       sofia, aug 20 (bta) the german tourist operator neckermann  has
 invested 5 million deutschemarks (some 600 million leva) in the
 renovation of bulgarian coastal hotels in the form of prepaid
 services.

       the company turns over between 40 and 45 million deutschmarks on     
 the bulgarian market.

       the teamwork with neckerman, bulgaria's largest partner on the
 german holiday market, was presented at a news conference at the
 holiday club riviera near varna. journalists of 'berliner zeitung,'
 'frankfurter neue presse' and 'frankfurter rundschau' attended the
 u a session.

       neckermann manager for eastern europe herbert ronchevich noed
 the company's interest in the bulgarian market. neckermann is booking
 some 60,000 customers for holidays in bulgaria per season, and this
 summer it has sold almost 70,000 vacations. the tendency has been
 upward since 1991.

       committee of tourism presldent vassil velev commended
 cooperation with neckermann.

       he said that the total number of visitors by mid-august was 5
 per cent up from the same date last year. the number of overnighs
 has increased by 11 per cent, and the number of foreign
 holiday-makers, by 13 per cent.
 [end] mi

