From: ecodefense@glas.apc.org
Newsgroups: reg.eeurope
Subject: urgent! campaign to stop NPP in Rus
Date: 22 Aug 1996 15:11:13 +0300

From: ecodefense@glas.apc.org (Vladimir Slivyak)
Subject: urgent! campaign to stop NPP in Russia!

From cci.glasnet.ru!ed Thu Aug 22 14:40:12 1996
Received: from cci.glasnet.ru(really [194.87.169.17]) by mail.glas.apc.org
	via sendmail with esmtp
	id  m0utXBK-00046GN@mail.glas.apc.org 
	for  ecodefense@glas.apc.org ; Thu, 22 Aug 1996 14:40:10 +0400 (WSU DST)
	(Smail-3.2 1996-Jul-4 #13 built DST-Aug-15)
Received: (from ed@localhost) by cci.glasnet.ru (8.6.12/8.6.9) id OAA03752; Thu, 22 Aug 1996 14:47:41 +0300
Date: Thu, 22 Aug 1996 14:47:37 +0300 (GMT+0300)
From: Vladimir Slivyak  ed@cci.glasnet.ru 
To: wiseamster@antenna.nl
cc: ecodefense@glas.apc.org
Subject: urgent! campaign against new NPP in Russia
Message-ID:  Pine.LNX.3.91.960822144701.3671B-100000@cci.glasnet.ru 
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; charset=US-ASCII
Status: RO


Rostov Nuclear Power Plant is about to be put into operation
STOP NUCLEAR MADNESS!
HELP US TO PREVENT A NEW CHERNOBYL!

Dear READERS of this message,
Russia is about to get a new potential Chernobyl!
Rostov Nuclear Power Plant is about to be put into operation.
Ex-USSR Antinuclear campaign is urgently asking you to help
put a stop to this nuclear plant.

I hope that almost everybody who reads this letter  already
knows  about  the antinuclear campaign's big victory
against nuclear shipping on the seas. Many of you helped us with
that.
As an organizer of this campaign I would like to note that this campa-
ign was  successful  thanks to several hundred people who read the mail
from the Ex-USSR Antinuclear campaign and ECODEFENSE! group.

But the "war" is not over yet.  Today I would like to ask you to  sup-
port  our  new  fax-campaign  against the proposed operation of Rostov
NPP!  Now the situation is crucial; and we all have the chance to  persuade
local  authorities not to make the decision to put the NPP into opera-
tion and commit a new crime against humankind and nature.  We need  to
influence  their  decision  and  it is very easy to do this - just send
your fax against the NPP to the fax-numbers which you can find on  the
second page.

It is very possible that we will be able to persuade local authorities
to give up their decision to put the NPP  into  operation  because  of
their  undefined  position.  We  should do this.  We know that nuclear
energy is in deep crisis in many countries.  It is very expensive  and
dangerous.  In Russia for the last several years the Ministry fo Atomic 
Energy (MinAtom) could not put into operation any of the proposed  new  
NPPs.  And now  everyone can make a difference and change the situation
by sending its fax. We should prevent MinAtom from the expansion of their 
activities. Otherwise they will continue to destroy our nature and spend 
our money on the creation of new NPPs.

Take action.  We know that the fax-campaign is a very  effective  tool
and we should use this tool.

Who and why doesn't want the operation of the Rostov NPP?

  Today Anti-Nuclear  Campaign  appeals to you to send your faxes aga-
inst Rostov NPP.  We are against all  nuclear  facilities  because  we
think that nuclear energy is expensive and  dangerous. Because  of 
its difficult economical situation, Russia is not able to develop its  
nuclear program.  Very soon we will need to shut down most of the 
existing nuclear reactors which will cost Russia about 3 billion dollars. 
Also the utilization  of exissting nuclear wastes is still an 
unresolvable problem and nobody knows how to deal with this problem.  At 
the same time Rostov  region  has very great energy potential including 
renewable energy sources. For these reasons Rostov region doesn't need 
nuclear energy!
 
    Anti-Nuclear Campaign works together with many  other  organisati-
ons. This action is organized with collaboration of organization "Gre-
en Don".  "Green Don" is professionally working against the Rostov NPP.
It  prepared  a report about the NPP and organized the public envi-
ronmental impact asessment. The asessment showed that the construction
of the NPP will seriously destroy the fish population in surrounding are-
as. It also showed that the construction was made with many violations.
Also  the  project for construction was designed in 1970 and therefore
has no protection systems.
   The population of all adjacent regions including regions of Ukraine
are strongly opposed to the construction. In last July local populati-
on organised several meeting against the operation of the NPP.
 
   Another organization which takes part in the  campaign  is  Rainbow
Keepers. They are organizing the protest camp near the NPP.


WHAT IS HAPPENING NOW
   The French company Electricite de France suggested local authorities
put the NPP in 1997.  The company is ready to give a credit to  fi-
nish  the construction and to take part in the construction using this
credit.  (Rostov region doesn't have money to finish the  plant).  Now
EdF  needs 350 mln dollars but it is evident that the sum will be big-
ger because French companies usually underestimate the expenses.
    First unit is ready on 95 %. The suggested type of reactor is the 
infamous VVR-1000. Only this year there were several accidents with
this type of reactor in Ukraine.

WHERE TO  SEND FAXES
   If you  would  like to know how to write your faxes we are ready to
give you an example.  Just send us a letter.  In your faxes we suggest
you politely ask local authorities not to make a decision about the
continuation of construction.  You should emphasize that the continua-
tion  will lead to a financial crisis and destroy nature and the health 
of surrounding population.
   
Local telephone code "8632"
Head of Rostov' regional administration - Vladimir Chub
Fax +7 (8632) 65-67-73,  66-21-20
Administration adviser on energy and fuel - Alexey Khomyakov
Fax +7 (8632) 65-12-84
Press-center of administration - Nadezhda Babich
Fax +7 (8632) 63-56-59
Chairman of local parliament - Alexander Popov
Fax +7 (8632) 63-58-91

ATTENTION! It's  extremely important that you send us copy of your
faxes,

Campaigner in Moscow: Vladimir Sliviak
Campaigner in Volgodonsk: Vladimir Lagutov

If you have not e-mail - send us copy of your fax to
tel/fax +7 (095) 298-30-87

For more  information contact russian representatives of Ex-USSR Anti-
nuclear campaign:
Moscow -  ed@cci.glasnet.ru , Tel/fax 7-095-2983087
Volgodonsk -  zedon@glas.apc.org 
Koenigsberg -  ecodefense@glas.apc.org , Tel/fax 7-0112-437286



