From: FIC@OLN.comlink.apc.org
Newsgroups: reg.eeurope
Subject: GAMA: bulgaria-plant
Date: 22 Aug 1996 14:02:00

Content-type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii

        GLOBAL ALTERNATIVE MEDIA ASSOCIATION - GAMA - PRESENTS:
        -------------------------------------------------------
                news provided via our member "infoPool"
                --------------------------------------

SOURCE: BTA
HEAD:   bulgaria to build waste treatment facilities

       sofia, august 21 (bta) - the contract on the construction of
 waste treatment facilities in the metallurgical plant in elisseina,
 northern bulgaria, will be signed by the year's end, 'continent'
 says.

       the first group of environmental experts of the japanese jci
 consultancy institute of metallurgy arrived here yesterday.

       they will prepare the tender dossiers and name the project           
 contractor. the construction will start in march 1997, and should be       
 completed after 39 months.

       the japanese experts guarantee that the facilities will
 minimize up to 90 per cent sulphur dioxide pollution of the air and
 95 per cent of the heavy metal pollutants of water and soil.

       an intergovernmental agreement to this effect was signed a year
 ago.  the agreement includes the elisseina plant and the nonferrous
 metal works in plovdiv, southern bulgaria.

       the environmental project will be funded by a japanese bank which    
 extended a credit of usd 20 million.
 [end] mps

