08/22 Rostov NPP  protest,  Volgodonsk,  Russia  (AAP)  -  the
special police   guard   of  Rostov  region,  central  russia,
attacked the camp of environmentalists on August  22's  night.
The environmentalists  organized  the  camp  to protest Rostov
Nuclear Power  Plant  start  up  proposed  by  1997.  Some  of
environmental activists were injured, nobody arrested.

08/26 Rostov  local  meeting of citizens,  Volgodonsk,  Russia
(AAP) -  the  local  environmental  groups  of  Rostov  region
organized the  meeting  of  local  citizens and authorities on
Monday in  Volgodonsk  city,  central  Russia.  Over  1000  of
participants expressed   to   local  government  the  opinions
against Rostov NPP' proposed start up.

08/27 Siberian Oil Project, BONN, Germany (AP) - The Worldwide
Fund  for Nature urged the World Bank on Tuesday to withhold a
planned loan for a  U.S.-  Russian  oil  venture  in  Siberia,
saying the project would harm the environment.

